sql:
SELECT experiment_id, access_type, session_id 
FROM experiment_access 
WHERE access_date = '2023-05-02' AND device_type = 'mobile';

SELECT data_point_id, experiment_id 
FROM data_points 
WHERE experiment_id = (SELECT experiment_id FROM experiments WHERE experiment_name = 'Nitrogen-Oxygen Reaction');

external_knowledge:
- "garden plots" metaphorically represents experiments; 
- "master gardener" refers to the user with user ID 1; 
- "kept the garden thriving" implies that the experiments are in an 'active' status;
- "seeds have sprouted" metaphorically represents the data points associated with those experiments.

sql:
SELECT species_name 
FROM chemical_species 
WHERE molecular_weight > 1.5;

SELECT LOG2(COUNT(*)) AS log2_count
FROM experiment_access
WHERE experiment_id = 0;

SELECT species_name 
FROM chemical_species
WHERE molecular_weight = (SELECT MAX(molecular_weight) FROM chemical_species);

SELECT users.user_name, experiment_access.access_type, experiment_access.ip_address
FROM experiment_access
INNER JOIN users ON experiment_access.user_id = users.user_id;
